<paragraph blockId="8.[902,1328,544,570]" box="[902,1328,544,570]" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">
<heading box="[902,1328,544,570]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="8" pageNumber="367" reason="2">
<taxonomicName authority="(K. Anderson, 1912)" baseAuthorityName="K. Anderson" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[902,1328,544,570]" class="Mammalia" family="Nycteridae" genus="Nycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="367" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="major">
<emphasis box="[902,1078,544,570]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">Nycteris major</emphasis>
(K. Anderson, 1912)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="367" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[809,1422,613,879]" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">
This species was previously recorded from Ziéla, Guinean 
<collectingRegion box="[915,995,647,673]" country="Liberia" name="Nimba" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">Nimba</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="FAHR, J." box="[1011,1146,647,673]" pageId="8" pageNumber="367" pagination="297 - 299" refId="ref13015" refString="FAHR, J. 2013 i. Nycteris major Dja slit-faced bat. Pp. 297 - 299, in The mammals of Africa. Volume IV: Hedgehogs, shrews and bats (M. HAPPOLD and D. C. D. HAPPOLD, eds.). Bloomsbury Publishing, London, 800 pp." type="book chapter" year="2013">
Fahr, 
<date box="[1079,1146,647,673]" pageId="8" pageNumber="367" value="2013-01">
2013 
<emphasis box="[1138,1146,647,673]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">i</emphasis>
</date>
</bibRefCitation>
). It is also known from the Iti 
<collectingRegion box="[893,958,681,707]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">River</collectingRegion>
(
<quantity box="[978,1061,681,707]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="367" unit="m" value="550.0">550 m</quantity>
), Liberian 
<collectingRegion box="[1197,1277,681,707]" country="Liberia" name="Nimba" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">Nimba</collectingRegion>
where Verschuren (1977) was not sure of its identification, listing it as either 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1903" box="[1015,1102,750,776]" class="Mammalia" family="Nycteridae" genus="Nycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="367" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arge">
<emphasis box="[1015,1102,750,776]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">N. arge</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<emphasis box="[1138,1247,750,776]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="K. Anderson" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[1138,1243,750,776]" class="Mammalia" family="Nycteridae" genus="Nycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="367" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="major">N. major</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
This specimen was later re-examined and determined to be 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="K. Anderson" baseAuthorityYear="1912" class="Mammalia" family="Nycteridae" genus="Nycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="367" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="major">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">N. major</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(J. Fahr, in litt.). However, it was not recorded during this study.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
